  <p>To ensure the editor's optimal operation, we recommend observing the following guidelines: </p> 
  <ul> 
   <li><p>Before <strong>importing an HTML page template</strong> in Adobe Campaign, please make sure the template opens and displays correctly in the various browsers.</p> </li> 
   <li><p>If the HTML page contains <strong>JavaScript scripts</strong>, they need to execute <strong>without errors</strong> outside of the editor. In general, avoid using scripts in message content to make sure it is correctly processed by email clients.</p> </li> 
   <li><p>When building a template, we recommend adding a <strong>'type'</strong> attribute to &amp;lt;input&amp;gt; tags. This information will be processed by the editor and help the user to link a database field to the form field when configuring the web application.</p> <p>Example of HTML code in the template: </p> 
    <codeblock gutter="true" class="syntax html">
      !!discoiqbr!!&lt;input&amp;nbsp;id="email"&amp;nbsp;type="email"&amp;nbsp;name="email"/&gt;!!discoiqbr!!&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 
    </codeblock><p>The official list of 'type' attributes is available at the following address: <a href="http://www.w3schools.com/tags/att_input_type.asp">http://www.w3schools.com/tags/att_input_type.asp</a></p> </li> 
   <li><p>Preview your messages before sending them. Adobe Campaign offers a way to test email rendering using Litmus. For more on this, see <a href="../../sending/using/email-rendering.md">Email rendering</a>.</p> </li> 
   <li><p>SCSS style sheets are not supported. Use regular CSS if you import ZIP files containing your HTML content.</p> </li> 
  </ul> 
  <p>More design and general best practices regarding messages are presented in the following Adobe Campaign step-by-step guide: <a href="https://docs.campaign.adobe.com/doc/standard/getting_started/en/ACS_DeliveryBestPractices.html ">Delivery best practices with Adobe Campaign</a>.</p> 
